  "text": "The complete chain from Deployment spec change to Pod creation in Kubernetes v1.32.0:\n\n1. DEPLOYMENT CONTROLLER RECONCILIATION (pkg/controller/deployment/deployment_controller.go:590)\n   The DeploymentController.syncDeployment() function is the main entry point. It gets triggered when a Deployment object is created or modified. It fetches the Deployment from the cache and delegates the reconciliation to the appropriate strategy (rolling update or recreate).\n\n2. REPLICASET CREATION (pkg/controller/deployment/sync.go:138-224)\n   DeploymentController.getNewReplicaSet() creates a new ReplicaSet that matches the Deployment's pod template. At line 224, it calls: dc.client.AppsV1().ReplicaSets(d.Namespace).Create(ctx, &newRS, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n   This sends a create request to the API server, which stores the ReplicaSet in etcd.\n\n3. REPLICASET CONTROLLER RECONCILIATION (pkg/controller/replicaset/replica_set.go:675)\n   When the ReplicaSet is created, the ReplicaSetController.syncReplicaSet() function is triggered. It checks if the ReplicaSet needs to be synced by comparing the expected pod count with the actual running pods.\n\n4. POD CREATION MANAGEMENT (pkg/controller/replicaset/replica_set.go:569)\n   ReplicaSetController.manageReplicas() calculates the difference between desired replicas and current pods. If pods need to be created, at line 598 it calls: rsc.podControl.CreatePods(ctx, rs.Namespace, &rs.Spec.Template, rs, metav1.NewControllerRef(rs, rsc.GroupVersionKind))\n\n5. POD CREATION IN CONTROLLER (pkg/controller/controller_utils.go:530-582)\n   RealPodControl.CreatePods() is a wrapper that delegates to CreatePodsWithGenerateName(). The actual creation happens in createPods() at line 582: r.KubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n   This sends HTTP POST requests to the API server to create Pod objects.\n\n6. API SERVER POD STORAGE (pkg/registry/core/pod/storage/storage.go:72)\n   NewStorage() creates the REST storage for Pods. It initializes a genericregistry.Store with CreateStrategy set to registrypod.Strategy. The store handles the HTTP request, validates the Pod, and stores it in etcd.\n\n7. API SERVER POD CREATION STRATEGY (pkg/registry/core/pod/strategy.go:86)\n   podStrategy.PrepareForCreate() is called by the API server's generic registry before storing the Pod. It:\n   - Sets Pod status to 'Pending'\n   - Computes the QoS class\n   - Drops disabled pod fields based on feature gates\n   - Applies scheduling gated conditions and pod affinity mutations\n\nTHE COMPLETE CALL CHAIN:\nDeployment Spec Change → syncDeployment → getNewReplicaSet → ReplicaSet.Create() → ReplicaSetController.syncReplicaSet → manageReplicas → CreatePods → createPods → Pod.Create() → API Server Pod Storage → podStrategy.PrepareForCreate\n\nThis chain demonstrates how Kubernetes implements the declarative reconciliation pattern: a Deployment object specifies the desired state, which the controllers transform through intermediate ReplicaSet objects to achieve the final desired Pod state. Each controller watches for changes in its relevant objects and reconciles the actual state towards the desired state."
